channel.title: Compile. ''Cannot find the Searchway''
channel.description:
I was trying to make me the owner [login.java], though when i try to compile, it says ''Cannot find the Searchway'', or if there are any swedish out there... ''det går inte att hitta sökvägen.''
Please come with suggestions or solutions >P

item.title: Compile. ''Cannot find the Searchway''
item.dc:creator: @jc22493 Jc22493
item.description:
@jc22493 wrote:

[quote=“x blitz x, post:11, topic:262716”][quote author=jc22493 link=topic=346946.msg2672885#msg2672885 date=1234901528]

click edit and delete all in your compiler then replace with this…

@echo off if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit

He’s using a 508. That compiler isn’t compatible with 508’s.

LOL?
A compiler compiles Java files. It doesn’t matter about anything else, as long as the Java file contains 0 errors and has the extension .java it’ll compile.

I’ve always thought that 508’s needed special compilers. I learn something every day.
[/quote]
Naa, every Java file compiles the same way.[/quote]
Mmk.
